 Urry  ."]}]},{"name":"Herbert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, introduced to Britain by the Normans. It is derived from <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’. An Old English form, <i>Herebeorht</i>, existed in England before the Conquest, but was superseded by the Norman form, which gave rise to an important surname. The family in question were earls of Pembroke in the 16th and 17th centuries; they included the poet  George Herbert . By the end of the Middle Ages <i>Herbert</i> was little used, although it remained a favourite with some families, notably the Saint Quintins of East Yorkshire. Its greater frequency in Britain from the 19th century onwards is due partly to the trend for the revival of medieval names of Germanic origin and partly to the trend for the transferred use of surnames."],"variants":[{"name":"Heribert","meanings":["From an Old French name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, introduced to Britain by the Normans. It is derived from <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’. An Old English form, <i>Herebeorht</i>, existed in England before the Conquest, but was superseded by the Norman form, which gave rise to an important surname. The family in question were earls of Pembroke in the 16th and 17th centuries; they included the poet  George Herbert . By the end of the Middle Ages <i>Herbert</i> was little used, although it remained a favourite with some families, notably the Saint Quintins of East Yorkshire. Its greater frequency in Britain from the 19th century onwards is due partly to the trend for the revival of medieval names of Germanic origin and partly to the trend for the transferred use of surnames."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Herbert de Orreby was born about 1085, in Orby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom. She married Herbert de Orreby IV. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"about 1085–":"umbes 1085–Surnud","1089–Male":"1089–Surnud","1110–1150":"1110–1150","1085–Female":"1085–Surnud","about 1085":"umbes 1085","Abt 1110":"umbes 1110","1089":"1089","1110":"1110","1085":"1085","1150":"1150","Orby, Spilsby, Lincolnshire, England":"Orby, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Orby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Orby, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1085–":"noin 1085–Kuollut","1089–Male":"1089–Kuollut","1110–1150":"1110–1150","1085–Female":"1085–Kuollut","about 1085":"noin 1085","Abt 1110":"noin 1110","1089":"1089","1110":"1110","1085":"1085","1150":"1150","Orby, Spilsby, Lincolnshire, England":"Orby, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Orby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Orby, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1085–":"environ 1085–Décédée","1089–Male":"1089–Décédé","1110–1150":"1110–1150","1085–Female":"1085–Décédée","about 1085":"environ 1085","Abt 1110":"environ 1110","1089":"1089","1110":"1110","1085":"1085","1150":"1150","Orby, Spilsby, Lincolnshire, England":"Orby, Lincolnshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Orby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Orby, Lincolnshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Herbert de Orreby est née environ 1085, à Orby, Lincolnshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé Herbert de Orreby IV. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"about 1085–":"um 1085–Verstorben","1089–Male":"1089–Verstorben","1110–1150":"1110–1150","1085–Female":"1085–Verstorben","about 1085":"um 1085","Abt 1110":"um 1110","1089":"1089","1110":"1110","1085":"1085","1150":"1150","Orby, Spilsby, Lincolnshire, England":"Orby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom","Orby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Orby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Herbert de Orreby wurde um 1085 in Orby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom geboren. Sie hat Herbert de Orreby IV geheiratet. Sie